{"key":"post-7582240","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7582240</id>\n<content>It doesn't get your floor wet because you drain the perlite first.  Perlite doesn't fall out through 1/4&quot; holes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The purpose of the holes is natural convection that humidifies the air and helps to provide air exchange.  A rubbermaid/sterlite type terrarium with 1/4&quot; holes drilled all over on all six sides will maintain mid 90's humidity, provided it has four inches or so of rinsed, then well drained perlite in the bottom.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7582277</next>\n<prev>7582238</prev>\n<first>6873558</first>\n<last>7582673</last>\n<when>1193883004</when>\n<utime>11/01/07 05:10 AM</utime>\n</post>"}